 41	// have a dedicated `.error` key use it; the rest reuse their `.required` key for
 42	// the invalid-type case (the old zod schemas pointed those at `.error` keys that
 43	// never existed, which rendered blank — reusing `.required` is the safe copy).
 44	// `.annotateKey({ messageMissingKey })` covers the absent-field case (the old
 45	// zod `required_error` fired for both empty and absent values); `.check` covers
 46	// the empty-string case; the node-level `message` covers the invalid-type case.
